individual and stylish in Burgundy.  Long based in the
village of Nuits-St.-Georges, the Chevillon wines
epitomize the rich, intense style for which this southern
end of the Côte d'Or is renowned.  These are lush,
hedonistic Burgundies that, year in and out, admirably
express the vineyards from which they issue.  The dense

Pape in 1896, motivated by a visionary confidence in the
quality and distinctiveness of the region's wines.  Since then,
the domaine has remained at or near the top of the
Châteauneuf du Pape hierarchy owing to its umblemished
record of consistency and quality.  Suffice it to simply state that
Clos des Papes is perhaps thestandard bearer for traditional,
Clos des Papes has always produced a single cuvée of red, a
classic blend of roughly two-thirds Grenache with other
authorized varietals.  Though the exact portion of each varietal
is vintage-specific, the wine always includes a hefty portion of
Mourvèdre which contributes to the wine's distinctive structure
and depth.  Along with Rayas and Bonneau, Clos des Papes

The white,first produced in 1955, typically combines equal
parts of Châteauneuf's six authorized white varietals: Grenache
Blanc, Roussanne, Bourbelenc, Clairette, Picpoul, and Picardin.
